 by minimising the volatility of income streams.
 If conspicuous consumption were truly futile, then there would be no way
 for the rational consumer to derive any utility from status-related consumption.
 The explicit subjective uncertainty - represented with a probability weighting
 function - models the advantage one receives from status consumption and
 allows the representative consumer to deviate from her long-term plans.
 The idea that a consumer may deviate from her long-term plans is a paradigm
 often used in the behavioural implementations of life-cycle methods.
 Here a particularly relevant approach is provided by Thaler et al
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ShefrinThaler1988"
literal "true"

\end_inset

